title: Red Bull 'open' to continuing with Renault engines
text: Photo: Luca Bruno, AP Red Bull team principal Christian Horner leaves the FOM building after talking with Formula One Group's Chief Executive Bernie Ecclestone, at the 'Sochi Autodrom' Formula One track , in Sochi, Russia, Friday, Oct. 9, 2015. Two years ago, Red Bull was unbeatable in Formula One. Now it could pull out of the sport altogether. Red Bull team principal Christian Horner leaves the FOM building... SOCHI, Russia (AP) — Red Bull team principal Christian Horner said Friday that he hopes his team will continue to race in Formula One next year and indicated it might even carry on using Renault engines.
